# .NET Coding Standards

## Code Style

- Use C# 12+ with file-scoped namespaces
- Follow .NET naming conventions (PascalCase for public members, _camelCase for private fields)
- All public members must have XML docs
- Prefer records for DTOs and value objects
- Use `var` only when the type is obvious from the right side

## Architecture

- **Framework**: .NET 8+ with ASP.NET Core
- **ORM**: Entity Framework Core with code-first migrations
- **Testing**: xUnit + FluentAssertions + NSubstitute
- **API Style**: Minimal API with endpoint grouping

## Build and Test

```bash
dotnet restore          # Restore packages
dotnet build            # Build solution
dotnet test             # Run all tests
dotnet run --project src/Api  # Start API server
dotnet ef database update     # Apply migrations
```

## Project Structure

```
src/
  Api/              # Minimal API endpoints, middleware, DI setup
  Domain/           # Entities, value objects, domain events
  Application/      # Use cases, DTOs, interfaces
  Infrastructure/   # EF Core, external services, repositories
tests/
  UnitTests/        # xUnit unit tests
  IntegrationTests/ # Integration tests with TestContainers
```

## Conventions

- API endpoints follow REST: `GET /api/users`, `POST /api/users`, `GET /api/users/{id}`
- Error responses use ProblemDetails (RFC 9457)
- Configuration is validated at startup via Options pattern with `IValidateOptions<T>`
- Never edit EF Core generated migration files
- One class per file, filename matches class name
